I am trying to write a script that will

1. Search for specific string in the file that is located in each user profile on C:\users\USERNAME\AppData\Roaming\Nextcloud\nextcloud.cfg
2. If the string
   &lt;pre&gt;
   &quot;[BWLimit]&quot;,&quot;downloadLimit=250&quot;,&quot;uploadLimit=250&quot;,&quot;useDownloadLimit=1&quot;,&quot;useUploadLimit=1&quot;
   &lt;/pre&gt;
   exists the file should not be touched 
3. If the string does not exists it should add it

What I did till now is that I made a script, using examples from this great site, that works BUT it only works when I trigger it locally. I need the script to work remotely (I use PDQ to push the script)

The script is as follows

```
$content = Get-Content &quot;C:\users\$($env:USERNAME)\AppData\Roaming\Nextcloud\nextcloud.cfg&quot;
$sites   = &quot;[BWLimit]&quot;,&quot;downloadLimit=250&quot;,&quot;uploadLimit=250&quot;,&quot;useDownloadLimit=1&quot;,&quot;useUploadLimit=1&quot;

if (!(Test-Path &quot;C:\users\$($env:USERNAME)\AppData\Roaming\Nextcloud\nextcloud.cfg&quot;)) {
    New-Item -Path &quot;C:\users\$($env:USERNAME)\AppData\Roaming\Nextcloud&quot; -Name nextcloud.cfg -Type &quot;file&quot;
} else {
    foreach ($site in $sites) {
        if (-not ($content -contains $site)) {
            $site | Out-File &quot;C:\users\$($env:USERNAME)\AppData\Roaming\Nextcloud\nextcloud.cfg&quot; -Append -Encoding utf8
        }
    }
}
```

I am using [bootstrap table][1]. I&#39;m also using its extension *Cookie* (but chose the localStorage method). Whenever I change the sorting, page number and such, this data is stored in localStorage and the state of the table is the same after refresh. Unfortunately, it doesn&#39;t save the active columns. 

So, whenever I uncheck a column in the dropdown and thus hide it, it isn&#39;t being saved in localStorage. (It does work in the documentation and examples for cookies though, as shown [here][2].)

I wasn&#39;t able to figure out the differences in the HTML, so I since tried solving it otherwise.

My approach is to save the `data-field` attributes of the current visible columns in an array in local storage (via JSON.stringify), whenever an item is checked/unchecked in the dropdown. And upon refresh, try looping through the array and make use of Bootstrap-Table&#39;s `showColumn`. 

This, however, ends in my browser crashing after getting countless of these: 
`[Violation] Added non-passive event listener to a scroll-blocking &lt;some&gt; event. Consider marking event handler as &#39;passive&#39; to make the page more responsive. See &lt;URL&gt;`

